column3: ADSL core variables are carried through all ADaM Datasets. See Core Variable column on the ADSL specs for variables kept on all ADaM datasets

column9: After sorting dataset by the KEYS, set to 1 for the first record per subject, then incremented by 1 for each subsequent record.

If AVAL is based on dates (AESI start date or end date) from a record in ADAESI dataset, set to "ADAESI".
If AVAL is based on dates from a record in ADAE dataset (AE start or end date), set to "ADAE".
If AVAL is based on dates from ADSL (e.g. a record is created because a subject is in the safety population, but no applicable record exists for that subject in ADAESI, or the AE does not resolve) then set to "ADSL"

If PARAM starts with "Time to Onset" then set to "Time to Onset"
Otherwise, if PARAM starts with "Time to Resolution" then set to "Time to Resolution"

For parameters pertaining to Nivolumab AESIs (PARAMCD starting with text "TTON" or "TTRN"), set to "Nivolumab"
For parameters pertaining to Relatlimab AESIs (PARAMCD starting with text "TTOR" or "TTRR"), set to "Relatlimab"
For parameters pertaining to Ipilimumab AESIs (PARAMCD starting with text "TTOI" or "TTRI"), set to "Ipilimumab"
For parameters pertaining to XL092 AESIs (PARAMCD starting with text "TTOX" or "TTRX"), set to "XL092".
For PARAMCD = 'TTODCTRT' set to "AE - Treatment Disc"
Set to the name of the AESI term used for populating PARAM.
Assigned based on PARAMCD, as per the codelist
PARAMCD is assigned according to the codelist, to align with the PARAM value assigned (see VLM for PARAM).
